      • hasWffConstraintViolations

        public boolean hasWffConstraintViolations(CycAccess access,
                                          ElMt mt)
        Description copied from interface: FormulaSentence
        Is this sentence inconsistent with any of its constraints (e.g. predicate argument constraints)? A false return value does not mean that this meets all the constraints, but it means that it is not inconsistent with them. For example, if an argument position is constrained to be a spec of #$Mammal, and the argument is merely known to be a spec of #$Animal, then the argument does not meet all of the constraints, but there are no constraint violations, and this method should return false.
        Specified by:
        hasWffConstraintViolations in interface FormulaSentence
        Returns:
        true if violations are found
